<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1881" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1881">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/64.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Minister of China</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s note No.
                            48, dated the 4th ultimo, in relation to a bill pending in the National
                            Assembly of Panama, for the exclusion of Chinese from that Republic, I
                            have the honor to enclose herewith, for your information, an extract
                            from despatch No. 397, dated January 30, 1915, and a copy of despatch
                            No. 400, dated February 5, 1915, from the American Minister to Panama,
                            showing the status of the bill on the latter date.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>